DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Hey, I'm having a lot of trouble with recursion and understanding the stack. I've been over it with TA's and read the book a bunch of times. I just can't seem to visualize any of it."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Mark

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "I've already talked it through with so many TAs, none of you can seem to help me..."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Mark

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "OOOOHHHHHHH!!!! I get it now! I just couldn't visualize it. Thank you so much! You just saved my GPA!"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Mark

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Everything on the internet is too complex. Isn't it your job to help me? I wouldn't have wasted my time coming here if I knew you were just gonna have me google it."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Mark

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "I'm sorry...are you encouraging me to cheat?! I might have to report you for that. I do need help but thats a bit extreme...."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Mark

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Well let's talk through the problem again, and we can take it step by step."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "How about we go to the whiteboard and we can draw some stack diagrams and pictures."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Have you checked on the internet? There are lots of great resources available. I struggle with this material as well so I wont be much help."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Oh don't worry about understanding that stuff, you can just copy off my solution from when I took this class."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: *How should I help this student understand recursion and stacks*
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "I don't understand how for loops could be used in this problem...can you help? Please?"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Sam

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Wait how does recursion work?"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Sam

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "I dont have a problem visualizing the assignment. I just don't understand how to actually implement any of this."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Sam

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "The textbook is so dry and boring. And the lecture slides are all about visualization which I don't have an issue with."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Sam

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Oh breaking it down makes it so much simpler. Thanks for your help!"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Sam

choices.string: "You just have to call a function within itself"

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "For loops are useless, recursion is where it's at!"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Lets try going to the board! Maybe visualizing it will help you understand the problem you are solving."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Have you tried looking through the textbook or the lecture slides?"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Let's work through some simpler examples on your computer first. Then we can build on that overtime to solve the whole problem!"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: *How should I go about teaching them for loops?*
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Sam

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "I want answers! I dont understand this and I'm an angsty teenager who has problems that people like you would never understand."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: August

choices.string: Figure out why they are upset

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: They tell you that they procrastinated their homework because they thought they knew everything but now that they actually tried starting it, they realize they dont understand anything.
They leave the room for 5-10 minutes and when they return they are much calmer and not talking like a poorly written character.
*As much as I may want to. I really shouldn't slap the students, I might get fired or charged with assault*
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Thanks for the answers! Now I've devloped a dependance on the TAs to solve all my problems and do my homework for me. I'm gonna tell my friends. See you next week!"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: August

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: *That probably wasn't the best idea. I'm just gonna rewind time to before I gave that answer and try again*
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: *This kid cleary needs some help badly, what should I do?*
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: You walk through identifying the problem with them and get them started on solving it on their own. They apologize for being belligerent earlier and thank you for your help!
"This homework is so confusing, I dont understand any off it. This class is so stupid and frustrating, they don't teach us anything. Can you help me?"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Megan

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Well the book is super confusing and I don't actually have lecture notes because I haven't been in weeks..."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Megan

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "You look like you just spaced out...can you help me or not?"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Megan

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "I don't even have any specific problems. I dont understand the entire thing! Unless you are gonna walk through the whole assignment I don't think you'll be of much help."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Megan

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Okay so nothing in the spec makes any sense. I don't know any of the terms used."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: Megan

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "What is it you're having trouble with? And have you looked through the book or at your lecture notes at all?"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: *I REALLY am not allowed to do anything of that sort*
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "How about we take some of the problems you might be having and try to work through some examples on the board?"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "How about we look through the spec a bit and you can point out all the parts you dont understand. Then I can work through them with you!"
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "Well first of all, you should definitely be going to class. Luckily it's not too busy today so I can give you a quick crash course on the information. But this should not be a regular thing."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: "I am here to help teach you, but you shouldn't be getting your first introduction to the material from the TAs, thats what lectures are for."
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: *How should I help the student?*
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA

DialogueEditorPhaseObject.text: You give the student a quick overview on the material they missed, and they promise to work harder on getting to class!
You feel the specter of feared incompetence seize upon you, and you are filled with terror.
You cannot leave until you've helped all the students!
Woohoo! Now that I've helped all the students, the gates of hell have opened once again and I can finally leave this prison!
DialogueEditorPhaseObject.name: TA
